# Public-surface filter — issue #219 (pre-publish security gate).
#
# Paths marked `export-ignore` are stripped by `git archive`, so they are
# excluded from the filtered flat-snapshot that the publish workflow
# (.forgejo/workflows/publish-public.yml) pushes to the PUBLIC GitHub mirror.
#
# The PRIVATE Forgejo repo keeps EVERYTHING; only the public surface is
# filtered. This is the single list to maintain — add one line per new
# org-internal path so the private repo and the public mirror cannot drift.
#
# A safety-net check in the publish workflow hard-fails if any of these paths
# ever appears in the produced snapshot, so a typo here cannot silently leak.

# --- Org-internal agent workflow + CI/deploy automation -------------------
# (bot identities, Hermes webhook, runner hosts, deploy targets)
.forgejo/                  export-ignore
CLAUDE.md                  export-ignore
AGENTS.md                  export-ignore
docs/agent-workflow.md     export-ignore
docs/releasing.md          export-ignore

# --- Org-internal deployment ----------------------------------------------
# (internal RFC1918 IPs, hostnames, reverse-proxy/TLS topology; the public
#  equivalents are docs/self-hosting.md / docker-compose.yml / .env.example)
docs/deployment.md         export-ignore
docker-compose.staging.yml export-ignore
docker-compose.prod.yml    export-ignore
docker-compose.landing.yml export-ignore
.env.staging               export-ignore
.env.production            export-ignore

# --- Internal design assets -----------------------------------------------
# (mockups + visual-regression harness reference real internal services/brand)
mockups/                   export-ignore
web/visual/                export-ignore

# --- Vendored third-party assets (#349) -----------------------------------
# TOAST UI Editor, kept pristine (do not hand-edit upstream). Exclude from the
# whitespace gate (`git diff --check`) and from language stats.
SuperStatus.Web/wwwroot/lib/**  -whitespace linguist-vendored
